3A233 Mass spectrometers, other than those specified in 0B002.g., capable of measuring ions of 230 u or greater and having a resolution of better than 2 parts in 230, as follows, and ion sources therefor:
3A233.a Inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometers (ICP/MS);
3A233.b Glow discharge mass spectrometers (GDMS);
3A233.c Thermal ionisation mass spectrometers (TIMS);
3A233.d Electron bombardment mass spectrometers having both of the following features:
3A233.d.1 A molecular beam inlet system that injects a collimated beam of analyte molecules into a region of the ion source where the molecules are ionised by an electron beam; and
3A233.d.2 One or more 'cold traps' that can be cooled to a temperature of 193 K (-80 °C);
3A233.e Not used;
3A233.f Mass spectrometers equipped with a microfluorination ion source designed for actinides or actinide fluorides.
3A233 Technical Notes: 1. Electron bombardment mass spectrometers in 3A233.d. are also known as electron impact mass spectrometers or electron ionisation mass spectrometers. 2. In 3A233.d.2., a 'cold trap' is a device that traps gas molecules by condensing or freezing them on cold surfaces. For the purposes of 3A233.d.2., a closed-loop gaseous helium cryogenic vacuum pump is not a 'cold trap'.

3A504 Cryogenic cooling systems and components, as follows:
