8A001 Submersible vehicles and surface vessels, as follows:
8A001 N.B. For the control status of equipment for submersible vehicles, see: Category 6 for sensors; Categories 7 and 8 for navigation equipment; Category 8A for underwater equipment.
8A001.a Manned, tethered submersible vehicles designed to operate at depths exceeding 1000 m;
8A001.b Manned, untethered submersible vehicles having any of the following:
8A001.b.1 Designed to 'operate autonomously' and having a lifting capacity of all of the following:
8A001.b.1.a 10 % or more of their weight in air; and
8A001.b.1.b 15 kN or more;
8A001.b.2 Designed to operate at depths exceeding 1000 m; or
8A001.b.3 Having all of the following:
8A001.b.3.a Designed to continuously 'operate autonomously' for 10 hours or more; and
8A001.b.3.b 'Range' of 25 nautical miles or more;
8A001.b Technical Notes: 1. For the purposes of 8A001.b., 'operate autonomously' means fully submerged, without snorkel, all systems working and cruising at minimum speed at which the submersible can safely control its depth dynamically by using its depth planes only, with no need for a support vessel or support base on the surface, sea-bed or shore, and containing a propulsion system for submerged or surface use. 2. For the purposes of 8A001.b.3.b., 'range' means half the maximum distance a submersible vehicle can 'operate autonomously'.
8A001.c Unmanned submersible vehicles, as follows:
8A001.c.1 Unmanned submersible vehicles having any of the following:
8A001.c.1.a Designed for deciding a course relative to any geographical reference without real-time human assistance; or
8A001.c.1.b Acoustic data or command link;
8A001.c.1.c Not used;
8A001.c.2 Unmanned submersible vehicles, not specified in 8A001.c.1., having all of the following:
8A001.c.2.a Designed to operate with a tether;
8A001.c.2.b Designed to operate at depths exceeding 1000 m;
8A001.c.2.c Having any of the following:
8A001.c.2.c.1 Designed for self-propelled manoeuvre using propulsion motors or thrusters specified in 8A002.a.2.; or
8A001.c.2.c.2 Fibre optic data link;
8A001.d Not used;
8A001.e Ocean salvage systems with a lifting capacity exceeding 5 MN for salvaging objects from depths exceeding 250 m and having any of the following:
8A001.e.1 Dynamic positioning systems capable of position keeping within 20 m of a given point provided by the navigation system; or
8A001.e.2 Seafloor navigation and navigation integration systems, for depths exceeding 1000 m and with positioning "accuracies" to within 10 m of a predetermined point;
8A001.f Not used;
8A001.g Not used;
8A001.h Not used;
8A001.i Not used.

