8A002.b.1 Enabling a vehicle to move within 10 m of a predetermined point in the water column;
8A002.b.2 Maintaining the position of the vehicle within 10 m of a predetermined point in the water column; or
8A002.b.3 Maintaining the position of the vehicle within 10 m while following a cable on or under the seabed;
8A002.b Technical Note: For the purposes of 8A002.b., 'automated control' systems apply to systems onboard submersible vehicles.
8A002.c Fibre optic pressure hull penetrators;
8A002.d Underwater vision systems having all of the following:
8A002.d.1 Specially designed or modified for remote operation with a submersible vehicle; and
8A002.d.2 Employing any of the following techniques to minimise the effects of back scatter:
8A002.d.2.a Range-gated illuminators; or
8A002.d.2.b Range-gated "laser" systems;
8A002.e Not used;
8A002.f Not used;
8A002.g Light systems specially designed or modified for underwater use, as follows:
